    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-08-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="287"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                <head>287. Memorandum From the Department of State Executive Secretary (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BWH2" type="from">Brubeck</persName>) to the President’s Special
                    Assistant for National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_BMG2" type="to"
                        >Bundy</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d287fn1">Source: Kennedy
                        Library, National Security Files, Countries Series, British Guiana II. Top
                        Secret. A copy was sent to Burdett.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-08-08">August 8, 1962</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>British Guiana</item>
                </list>
                <p>At a meeting this afternoon between Mr. <persName corresp="#p_JUA1"
                        >Johnson</persName> and Mr. <persName>Helms</persName> it was agreed that we
                    would propose to the British a specific agenda for the <pb facs="0614" n="582"
                        xml:id="pg_582"/> talks next week on British Guiana. The objective is to
                    bring matters to a head by forcing a consideration of political factors [<hi
                        rend="italic">1 line of source text not declassified</hi>].</p>
                <p>The agenda is as follows:</p>
                <p>1. Assessment of the situation in British Guiana.</p>
                <p>[<hi rend="italic">4 paragraphs (4 lines of source text) not
                    declassified</hi>]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">E.S. Little</hi>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d287fn2">Little signed for <persName corresp="#p_BWH2"
                                >Brubeck</persName> above <persName corresp="#p_BWH2"
                                >Brubeck</persName>’s typed signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
